Package: rye
Type: Package
Title: A Lisp Dialect for R
Version: 0.0.1
Authors@R:
    person("William", "Brannon", email = "will.brannon@gmail.com",
           role = c("aut", "cre", "cph"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-1435-8535"))
Author: William Brannon
Maintainer: William Brannon <will.brannon@gmail.com>
Description: Rye is a Lisp dialect implemented in and with access to R,
    leveraging R's Scheme heritage to provide a homoiconic language with
    powerful macro capabilities and seamless R interoperability. Compatibility
    with older R versions is intended, but versions earlier than R 4.x have not
    been tested.
